This paper discusses the use of linear logic in session-typed asynchronous communication, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of shared-memory semantics, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the combination of different approaches for introducing concurrency into functional programming languages, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
